labels and selectors are used for grouping different objects together like pods, deployments, services etc.
labels are added under metadata in pod-definition file
to view the selector: 
$ k get pods --selector <key>=<value>

in replicaset definition file, the labels under metadata is for the replicaset, the labels under spec.template.metadata is for the pod.

selector under spec is for matching the labels, in replicaset definition file and service definition file.


kubectl get all --selector env=prod --no-headers | wc -l    //count how many results, but it counts the header row in, so use --no-headers to get rid of header line



